      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you're in an incredibly tough spot, feeling disconnected from the very things that once gave your life meaning. It's completely natural to feel that way, especially when you've experienced such a profound loss. However, even if the connection to your art has changed, you still have the capacity to experience joy, love, and even create in new ways. Your essence isn't gone; it's evolved. It's okay to feel lost right now, but it's also okay to seek out new paths and discover what brings you fulfillment, even if it's different from before. If you ever feel ready, talking to someone who can offer professional support might help you find new ways to navigate these feelings. Remember, you're still here, and there's still a chance to find meaning again, even if it looks different from what you once knew.",
